	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102890808611592>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102890808611592>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102890808611592>RE: Khukri quest.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102890808611592#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 9th 11:59 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=631><span id=Guru>Sir Parttime</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>142 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hail Talupus...<br><br>I could be a couple of different problems.&nbsp;&nbsp;First, the best place to camp the raiders is at the column at the edge of the swamp...turn left and follow the &quot;road&quot; as you enter the swamp from Cabilis.  Be careful, there are some tough frogloks, bandits, and assorted bugs and plants roaming the area.<br><br>Second, the raiders placeholders are anything that spawns near the edge of the water near the column.  I have been told that they tend to spawn at night, but in the swamp, how could you tell?  I don't know if that is true or not.<br><br>Depending on your level, I suggest bringing friends who can get experience hunting the area or a high level ranger to babysit (and track) in case of a Froglok knight or shammy shows up to break up the party.<br><br>In any event, this is a long camp.  I had the parts for the next two Khukri quest before I had the heart to start this one.  I guess that's why it is called the Khukri's Quest of Pain :-)<br><br>Good hunting fellow Iksar Knight of the Greenmist.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></td></tr>
