	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well there are a couple of easier options that Fear/Plane of Growth.&nbsp;&nbsp;First Thurgadin Quest Armor is better AC than Fear Armor and although slower to drop is easier to get 2 pickup groups in Kael Arena than to the Planes.<br><br>Second with a grood group you can get Royal Frosted Velium Armor from Icewell Keep, off the Dwarfs.  BP and Bracers are rare, everything else drops quickly and is also better stats than Fear Armor.<br><br>The last option would be Blood Ember armor, but you'll never get the BP or Legs from a pick-up group.  For Legs I'd try killing in Kael again and look for some of the Armor that drops there (non quest), Thunder Etched I think, stats are awesome but it's extremely rare.  Otherwise but some of the better Dragonhide Legs (23AC +STA or better).<br><br>For the BP start your epic.  Somewhere along the line you get a 42AC no drop BP that you can wear till you finish the epic.  Or look for Shissar Scale/Barbed Ringmail/Phased Spider Carcapace or save all your plat and buy Blood Ember BP.<br><br>I think you should rethink the Guild situation.  Guilds don't have to be that strong to do Plane of Fear and Plane of Hate.  And not all guilds are jerks.  Look around, you'll find some nice mid-size guilds that hopefully you like and enjoy playing with.  But then I don't know any guildsa on your server so I can't recommend any.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
