	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102865451356945>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102865451356945>RE: Race.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102865451356945#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Aug 6th 1:35 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.93]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If I had to pick between the 2 that you mentioned, it would be natural regen every day of the week and twice on Sunday.<br><br>Mana pool is vastly overrated.&nbsp;&nbsp;Granted, you want a certain minimum level to be able to survive your typical encounter, but, in general, the higher the mana pool, the longer the down time.  I have heard an argument that a higher mana pool is advantegous at the high end raids, as you get to med it all back before you continue, but Im not sure that I agree with that school of thought, as I have yet to see that actually take place, but some believe it as if was written in stone somewhere.<br><br>Mana pool isnt generally the problem, its mana regen that should be focused on.  Solve that problem and you will almost care less what your mana pool is.  For instance, once you have C3 on you, you will never want to be without it again.<br><br>As far as if I would want regen vs high INT or otherwise, that is a very challenging decision.  I think its absolutely hysterical when the high INT characters defend the attributes of INT like no tomorrow.  That is NOT the primary benefit of being those classes and they will lose that argument 99 out of 100 times.  <br><br>The primary benefit of being a ERU or a DE or a GNM, etc is the ability to level quicker.  All things being equal, a DE will always be higher level than an TRL or a IKS (or OGR for that matter).  That makes sense also.  The slowest leveling SK races are the ones with the most abilities / most stats; i.e. they are probably superior races.  A big however though is that they level far slower.  That is what balances the races out.  Would you rather have a higher level SK or one with more stats / abilities?  Makes for an interesting decision.<br><br>On that note, however, I have recently discovered that the xp is takes a small race SK to get the aa ability &quot;BASH&quot; exceeds the xp penalty for an ORG and TRL.  What one could then argue is that the ORG or TRL make the best SK races, but that is so far at the top end that it is almost NA.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
