	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=146349><span id=Scholar>DemitriAlexander</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>SK races....<br><br>Troll - Slam, Regen, but low int. Better for those SKs that plan on soloing, or being a main tank. Spells are almost useless (usually).<br><br>Ogre - Slam, Awesome starting str., but again, low int. Also good for tanking, less solo potential than trolls.<br><br>Iksar - About the same as a troll, statwise, regenwise, and int.wise.<br><br>Dark Elf - Good starting int., can tank if NEEDED, but (usually) better on the casting end of things. Soloing not a big problem, but alot of sitting time (at least you get med skill up)<br><br>Erudite - About the same as a Dark Elf, good for casting, lousy str. good if you can twink him with int. and str. boosting item, but that goes without saying for all SKs.<br><br>Human - No size bonus. No slam. No great starting stats, but none that are too low either. In my opinion, the best all-around SK.<br><br>The short race..... - OK, I know I'm being mean here, but I really can't see anyone under 4 feet tall being the physical manifestation of evil. I'm sorry, I know there are people who swear by short shadowknights, and I respect that, but I just think the game was better off without them.<br>Since I'm always on roleplay, I have never even attempted to play a short shadowknight, so I have no room to bash their stats at all, so all I can post here are my opinions, which some of you will like and some of you won't. Again, a Troll or Ogre Shadowknight will threaten you with awesome muscle, a Dark Elf or Erudite will threaten you with spells, a Human or Iksar will get you either way, but a midget? Maybe some people find them threatening, but not unless they're afraid of him gnawing off their ankles. lol.<br><br>And that's how I see the races.<br><br>Again, these are mostly my opinions, and should hold no sway over what race you play. Play the game for why it was created, for fun.<br><br>-DemitriAlexander</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
