	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have heard this school of thought &amp; I can tell you that quite a few have not considered all the facts.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since the now imfamous patch that improved 2H lvl bonus, people are starting to consider 2H weapons far more seriously.  This is a good thing.  By sacrificing AC, it only makes sense to have a 2H weapon do more damage than a comparable 1H weapon.<br><br>However, now people are just making absolutely silly claims &amp; clearly havent thought things through.  Claims like, &quot;Once you are over 55+, you should ALWAYS [emphasis added] be wielding a 2H,&quot; or &quot;...many of the 2H weapons in CT will outdamage ANY [emphasis added] 1H weapon.&quot;  I just about fell out of my seat with laughter reading this nonsense.<br><br>If you were running around with Black Rock Maul of Crushing, Eye of Rigtorgn, Soul Defiler, or the absolutely insane, Sledge of Smashing (&quot;SoS&quot;), you are in excellent shape.  I mean excellent.  The DPS on those is scary &amp; SoS will outdamge ALL but the most INSANE 2H weapons in the game (the huge difference maker for SoS is the 217 DD proc). <br><br>If those are too high end for you, then you can scale it back a little.  Shard of Night &amp; Massive Dragonclaw Shard are really nice (yes, Shard IS better then Massive 58+ due to the buffs) &amp; will dish out a nice DPS.  You will easily be doing damage on par with that of say a DiZok Imperial Katana with those weapons.<br><br>I am slow to advocate either 1H or 2H, as both have their pros &amp; cons.  Generally, however, you choice to wield either is probably more dependent on what you get access to.<br><br>At the end of the day, 1H is fine for 55+.  it all depends on what you get.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
