	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=10280707289795>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10280707289795>RE: Damn you Verant.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10280707289795#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jul 30th 7:25 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Im not sure I am understanding what these SKs are complaining about.<br><br>If they are saying that they are having trouble getting invited to raids, where they dont know anyone (or very few) and it isnt a raid that is initiated by their guild, then yeah, they are probably somewhat correct.&nbsp;&nbsp;Getting invited to go on raids is generally far more a function of what guild you are in and what friends you have, rather than what class you play, CLR included.<br><br>However, make no mistake about it, an SK will seldom, if ever, be as valuable on a raid as a CLR, BRD, DRD, ENC, etc, as WAR and PLD also make very effective tanks and certain buffs/songs are generally needed from the aforementioned classes.  A MNK also generally makes for a better puller than an SK.<br><br>Does this mean that SKs are not desired?  No.  As a matter of fact, as resounding no.  Each and every class brings something to the table.  But anyone who tells you that SKs are absolutely needed for raids and that groups go out of their way to find one all the time is either ignorant or is lying.<br><br>The SK bread and butter used to be their taunt ability (until super high experience, super raiding guilds where an SK gets equipment that is damn near the best in game and can tank almost on par with a WAR).  Per-nerf, an SK could grab agro off a careless WIZ for crying out loud.  With disease counters (not disease cloud) being nerfed, however, taunt ability, and therefore, some of the SK value, has gone down, regardless of how much some want to blow it off.  Quite simply, SKs cannot taunt anywhere near what they once could.  That sucks if you ask me.<br><br>I can assure you that Neptunis might be the beneficiary of a kind server if his statement that he can &quot;take agro off anyone whenever [he] wants it&quot; is true, especially at 56.  No way can you do that on mine.  Its a pain to take agro off some careless players, sometimes even off of players that are diligent in trying to not get agro.  What used to be a simple, one spell mem, super fast cast, low mana Disease cloud away from agro has morphed into a complicated decision making process of either SV, HF, etc (if I wanted the fasters casting agro spells which suck) or the long casting, high mana using cascading darkness (nice agro with this baby) or asytotle or drain spirit.  This is a big drawback because we only have 8 spell slots that could allow us to be doing other useful things for the group...<br><br>SKs are very self-sufficent classes that can tank very well and do many other things that other classes cant.  They are seldom the best at doing those things, but its the fact that they can do so many things decent to good that makes them appealing.  I enjoy playing my SK a great deal, but I have accepted the fact that SKs are not the best at doing any one thing.  Perhaps the old adage of &quot;Jack of all trades, master of none&quot; applies here.<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
