	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm going to have to chalk this 1 up to playing style.&nbsp;&nbsp;For me I can't understand how you can't get agro.<br><br>First, I never relied on disease cloud for taunt.  I've never needed to have a special spell to draw agro.  For me it's always been the oposite, I'm always making sure I don't get agro.  I'm always 1 cast away from being the most hated player in the zone (or so it seems) so whenever I want agro 1 cast of Shadow Vortex or Heart Flutter does it, even off the over eager Wizards.<br><br>I cast alot.  No other way to put it, I'm always debuffing, dotting or tapping whatever I'm fighting.  It's not uncommon for me to have 4 debuffs, 2 taps, FD and 1 dot up for a raid, and I use them all.  I am shocked when people say Shroud of Pain isn't an agro spell, that gets me hit every time, same with shroud of Hate.  Now Torrent of Hate isn't a big agro but the other 2 seem to always work for me.  I often have to FD right after I cast Shroud of Pain because I'll pull agro off the Main Tank on the next cast if I don't.  And I'm using either the Tae Eww War Hammer (33/36 +65HP's) or the Argent Defender so I'm not normally using what would be considered high agro weapons.<br><br>I really can't explain why I can always get agro if some of you are stuggling, but definately not being a big agro isn't going to keep you from being invited on Raids.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
