	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jul 21st 2:22 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=163478><span id= >Drom</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Having recently gotten my MoSS, I'm a huge fan of it.&nbsp;&nbsp;As far as the shield goes, I'm currently using a Crested Mistmoore Shield, and am a big fan of it (Ac10, Dex6, SvD10, SvP10, SvM10); the save-bonuses make it very appealing to me, and it can be gotten very cheaply; a Charred Guardian Shield is also a decent choice (Ac10, Wis9), and in the same price range, around 200-300pp.<br><br>I had the discussion about what the best way to work with haste items is with my guild last night, and I came to the following conclusion:  with Haste items being so highly in demand, you can probably start by purchasing the cheaper item (probably FBSS), and when you get a little more plat, working up the chain by selling the previous item and purchasing the new one.  With a little patience and business skill, you can probably make each exchange work out to your favor.<br><br>The FBSS is %21 haste, no other stats.  I was looking at the Silver Chitin Handwraps a little more seriously (AC10, 22%haste, a whole mess of small stats and saves bonuses),but there is an opinion that it is horrible for plate classes (which I'm not sure I concur with). Once you get past those two in price (SCHW between 4-5k), you're looking at things like Sash of the Dragonborn, Silvery Belt of Contention and the like until you broach into the realm of the truly ridiculous (Runed Bolster Belt, Cloak of Flames) which run in the range of well over 30k.<br><br>Just my two bits...<br><br>-Drom<br>40th level Shadow Knight on Quellious<br><br>&quot;Not the face! Not the face!&quot;</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
